# -- BISMUTH: Essentia Manipulation
planarartifice.research.essentia_manipulation.title=Essentia Manipulation
planarartifice.research.essentia_manipulation.stage.1=[WIP]
planarartifice.research.essentia_manipulation.stage.2=Eureka! I am finally free from the cumbersome method of individually crushing up Vis Crystals. by infusing a piece of Redstone Dust with arcane energy, I now have an easier way of making salis mundus.

# -- BISMUTH: Metal Transmutation
planarartifice.research.metal_transmutation.title=Metal Transmutation
planarartifice.research.metal_transmutation.stage.1=Bismuth is an interesting metal, It is malleable, inorganic, and seemingly unstable. I wonder if I could cause it to "crash" into other metals, such as gold...
planarartifice.research.metal_transmutation.stage.2=This could revolutionize underground resources forever. I have figured out the way to "nudge" the bismuth into other metals using part of the corresponding metal's essences.<BR>I must take note that this process is rather expensive, but makes use of excess essentia.

# -- BISMUTH: Reagent Transmutation
planarartifice.research.reagent_transmutation.title=Reagent Transmutation
planarartifice.research.reagent_transmutation.stage.1=There are still many items that are difficult or troublesome to obtain, and there are some items similar enough that I should be able to apply some simple alchemy to change between them.
planarartifice.research.reagent_transmutation.stage.2=The alchemy surely wasn't "simple", but the hunger for knowledge always finds a way. I have managed to convert a common eye into one of the otherworldly beings, and extract the essence of gunpowders - creating a powder full of energy. That does not mean there is more I can do to this concept.
planarartifice.research.reagent_transmutation.stage.3=Gotcha - in additions to the previous recipes, I have managed to create a way to forge the hellish rod from mundane items and a nice stew of essentia. Although I'll have to find another way to turn it back to the rod forms, as it can only create powders. Although this research has lead me into an interesting direction - The rare ores of the world. The link between them are thin, I acknowledge that I am reaching for the stars here. But... could it be done?
planarartifice.research.reagent_transmutation.stage.4=The answer was right in front of me all along. Now I have the ability to transmute between amber and quicksilver - unifying them into a singular matter.

